lego:evidence  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_4927  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: STORM imaging showed MDGA2 (the endogenous protein was replaced by recombinant tagged counterparts) co-localizes with Homer1c in cultured rat hippocampal neurons at DIV10 and DIV14. Related supplementary figures show validation of shRNA and rescue MDGA constructs in neuronal cultures. Authors note that \"AP-MDGA1 and AP-MDGA2 displayed a fairly uniform distribution at DIV 10 and 14, filling the whole dendritic shaft without specific accumulation at synapses, similarly to the negative control GFP-GPI (Figure 2A and C)\".\n\nMDGAs are GPI-anchored membrane molecules, hence \"anchored component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: result section; \"We then examined the sub-cellular surface distribution of endogenous MDGA1 in dissociated rat hippocampal cultures at different developmental stages (DIV 7, 14, 21), by performing live staining of neurons with MDGA1 antiserum before fixation and counter immuno-labelling of either MAP-2 as a dendritic marker, excitatory pre- and post-synaptic proteins VGLUT1 and PSD-95, or inhibitory pre- and post-synaptic markers VGAT and gephyrin, respectively (Figure 1F, I).\" -->> following result section and M&M, the same culture setup was used for STORM imaging in Figure 2\n\nantibody:\nfor STORM, the endogenous MDGA2 was replaced by a tagged protein \"AP-MDGA2\"\n\n\"DNA constructs\nRat V5-MDGA1, V5-MDGA2, HA-MDGA1, HA-MDGA2, shMDGA1, shMORB (shCTRL), sh-RNA resistant HA-MDGA1 (rescue) constructs as described previously (Elegheert et al., 2017; Pettem et al., 2013) were kind gifts from A.M. Craig (University of British Columbia, Vancouver, OR). Mouse AP-tagged NLGN1, biotin ligase (BirAER), shMDGA2, and mApple-V5-MDGA2 rescue plasmids (Loh et al., 2016) were gifts from A. Ting (Stanford University, CA). AP-MDGA1 and AP-MDGA2 were generated by replacing the V5 tag of the V5-MDGA1 and V5-MDGA2 constructs, respectively, by the 15 amino acids AP tag (5'-GGCCTGAACGATATCTTCGAGGCCCAGAAGATCGAGTGGCACGAG-3') using the HD-In-Fusion kit (Takara). The linker 5'-GGAGGATCAGGAGGATCA-3' was added after the AP tag. AP-MDGA1 and AP-MDGA2 rescue constructs were generated by inserting the mutations responsible for the resistance to the respective shRNAs obtained from HA-MDGA1 and mApple-V5-MDGA2 rescue constructs, respectively, using the HD-In-Fusion kit. HA-MDGA2 rescue was created by replacing the AP tag from the AP-MGDA2 rescue construct by the HA tag using the HD-In-Fusion kit.\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099031 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4927" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
